&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>It&amp;rsquo;s useful to know how many connections your web server can handle. It&amp;rsquo;s important to see how your server behaves under load. That&amp;rsquo;s why it&amp;rsquo;s necessary to benchmark it. We&amp;rsquo;ll see here how to benchmark it, and then we&amp;rsquo;ll look at some differences when using cache servers.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Ajaxterm: Using a Terminal via Web</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/ajaxterm-utiliser-un-terminal-en-web/</link><pubDate>Fri, 22 Apr 2011 13:44:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/ajaxterm-utiliser-un-terminal-en-web/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://antony.lesuisse.org/software/ajaxterm/" rel="external" target="_blank">Ajaxterm&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> allows you to have a terminal through a web page. For example, if you&amp;rsquo;re at a restricted site that doesn&amp;rsquo;t allow you to use SSH, there&amp;rsquo;s a good chance you can still use HTTPS. This is where Ajaxterm becomes handy, as it allows you to connect to the machine hosting Ajaxterm.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Collection3: A Web Interface for Collectd</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collection3_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</link><pubDate>Wed, 09 Jun 2010 21:58:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collection3_:_Une_interface_web_pour_Collectd/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/Collectd_:_Installation_et_configuration_de_Collectd/">Collectd&lt;/a> is great, but with a functional web interface, it&amp;rsquo;s even better. We&amp;rsquo;re going to see how to install &lt;a href="https://collectd.org/wiki/index.php/Collection3" rel="external" target="_blank">Collection3&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>, an interface that isn&amp;rsquo;t necessarily pretty, but is very functional.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Awstats: Setting up Awstats, a Web Logs Interpreter</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Awstats_:_Mise_en_place_d%27Awstats,_interpr%C3%A9teur_de_logs_web/</link><pubDate>Sun, 11 Apr 2010 15:51:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Awstats_:_Mise_en_place_d%27Awstats,_interpr%C3%A9teur_de_logs_web/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>AWStats is a web log analyzer (but also FTP, Streaming, and mail) offering static but also dynamic graphical views of access statistics for your web servers.&lt;br>
It displays the number of visits, unique visitors, pages, hits, transfers by domain/country, host, time, browser, OS, etc. It can be run using CGI scripts or command line.&lt;br>
AWStats is free software under the GPL license.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The installation of Awstats is simple: this software interprets Apache logs (all commands to which the server responded) to provide you with understandable graphs and tables in the form of a web page.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Mirroring a Website</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/aspirer-un-site-web/</link><pubDate>Sun, 20 Sep 2009 15:51:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/aspirer-un-site-web/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>There are software applications that allow you to mirror websites, but why use them when a simple command can do the same thing?&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="usage">Usage &lt;a href="#usage" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>To mirror mozilla.org for example, use this command:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="0224d48" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>wget --random-wait -r -p -e robots=off -U mozilla http://www.mozilla.org&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>-p: Include all files, images, etc.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>-e robots=off: Bypass the robot.txt file&lt;/li>
&lt;li>-U: Specify mozilla as the browser that will do the mirroring&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&amp;ndash;random-wait: Allows wget to randomize download times in seconds to avoid blacklists&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>Other useful parameters:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CSS: Style Sheets</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/CSS_:_Les_feuilles_de_style/</link><pubDate>Mon, 13 Oct 2008 19:48:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/CSS_:_Les_feuilles_de_style/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>When developing a style sheet, it is sometimes useful to apply a style to just one small element (e.g., the first line of a paragraph) or to an element with a certain behavior (e.g., a link being hovered over). Common selectors like &amp;ldquo;body&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;p&amp;rdquo;, or &amp;ldquo;h1&amp;rdquo; do not allow for such precise style application. There are in fact other types of selectors, called pseudo-formats or pseudo-classes, that allow for more refined styling.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Geolocation with Apache 2</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Geolocalisation_avec_Apache_2/</link><pubDate>Sun, 16 Mar 2008 08:41:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Geolocalisation_avec_Apache_2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>This guide explains how to set up &lt;a href="https://www.maxmind.com/app/mod_geoip" rel="external" target="_blank">mod_geoip&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> with Apache2 on a Debian Etch system. mod_geoip looks up the IP address of the client end user. This allows you to redirect or block users based on their country. You can also use this technology for your &lt;a href="https://www.openx.org/" rel="external" target="_blank">OpenX&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a> (formerly known as OpenAds or phpAdsNew) ad server to allow &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geo_targeting" rel="external" target="_blank">geo targeting&lt;svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">&lt;path fill="currentColor" d="M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z"/>&lt;/svg>&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Accelerating CGI Scripts with SpeedyCGI-PersistantPerl</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Acc%C3%A9l%C3%A9rer_les_scripts_CGI_avec_SpeedyCGI-PersistantPerl/</link><pubDate>Wed, 12 Sep 2007 22:12:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/Acc%C3%A9l%C3%A9rer_les_scripts_CGI_avec_SpeedyCGI-PersistantPerl/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction"